✔️ I have a quote I wanted to share: "A bird sitting on a tree is never afraid if the branch breaking because her trust is not on the branch, but on her own wings." When it comes to trust, this quote really resonates with me because it's so easy to forget the power of mobility we have as humans. So many of us show up to practice to strengthen our physical and emotional wings, and it's such a wonderful thing when we realize the more energy we have in our physical bodies, and the more emotional courage we have to say "no" to things, the stronger our wings become. And then we can go on the journey of happiness, sadness, ups and downs and enjoy it. I'd like to end this thought with another Zen proverb: "Let go or be dragged." If we don't strengthen our wings, we will feel anxiety by being in a constant reactive state to things happening to us. This is something I am still working on myself; the practice of letting go myself so that I don't allow myself to get dragged (as often) by things I need to detach from. The branch may fall, but our wings are strong and we will let go of the things that no longer serve us! 🙏 Namaste

Man, I keep forgetting to comment on the videos.  On a few you mentioned you were in an car accident.  I was in something similar.  I fell out the truck, and had to have surgery to stitch my leg up. Continued to have back pain, and I have been going to the chiropractor for weeks, and months.  My friend recommended I do Yoga, and I have been doing this since February; first started with your Dedicate series earlier this year.  I have noticed I've gotten toner, and lost weight. Hi Adrienne - I have been using your videos for the last month during an intense stretch of anxiety. I'm sorry that I took this long to write and to thank you. Thank you! Up until this point I have noticed the ways in which you tend to be very inclusive in your language with regards to gender and identity.  In this video though when you talk about your friend who said you have a "man voice" - I wanted to point out that there is no such thing as a "man voice" and that language could be offered with a more inclusive spriit. There are deeper voices that belong to people of ALL genders. Your friend seemed to imply that having a "man voice" was a bad thing? What about the many trans women whose voices resist changing and have a deeper voice? they are woman. So are you. I hope you will speak with your friend and also reconsider this comment! Thank you again. These videos are so incredibly helpful to me and so many others.
